https://codeforces.com/group/MWSDmqGsZm/contest/223338/problem/S    ----problem link


https://www.techcrashcourse.com/2015/11/c-program-to-check-whether-triangle-is-valid-or-not-given-sides.html    ----to check if the triangle is valid or not link



heron's formula = sqrt(s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)) where a,b,c are the three sides of the triangle and s=(a+b+c)/2

this formula would give the result correct 


if we know the base and height of the traingle we can calculate (height*base)/2=area
but here since sides are given we need to apply pythogras theorem on half of triangle to find height of the triangle then apply formula


but here we can do it more conveniently

CODE////


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
#define ll long long int
int main()
{
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(NULL);
    cout.tie(NULL);
    ll a,b,c;
    cin>>a>>b>>c;
    
      if((a+b)>c and (b+c)>a and (c+a)>b)
      {double s=(a+b+c)/2;
      double area=sqrt(s*(s-a)*(s-b)*(s-c));
      
      cout<<"Valid"<<endl;
      cout<<fixed<<setprecision(6)<<area<<endl;
      }
      else
        {cout<<"Invalid"<<endl;}
    
